+# XAUUSD H1 Swing Engine v2.1 Tuning Report
+
+> **Status:** development/validation evidence only. The 171 labels are an AI-assisted expert draft pending independent human adjudication, and no locked TEST split exists.
+
+## Objective
+
+Reduce the excessive local-pivot false positives produced by frozen v2.0 while retaining enough recall for downstream BOS and CHoCH processing. v2.0 remains the default version; v2.1 is opt-in.
+
+## Data governance
+
+- Benchmark: `XAUUSD_H1_AI_ASSISTED_EXPERT_DRAFT`
+- TRAIN: `XAUUSD_H1_001` through `XAUUSD_H1_008`
+- VALIDATION: `XAUUSD_H1_009` through `XAUUSD_H1_012`
+- TEST: none
+- Selection used TRAIN only; VALIDATION was scored after both parameters were fixed.
+
+## Selected profile
+
+| Parameter | Value |
+|---|---:|
+| Structural reversal threshold | 2.80 ATR |
+| Major/External prominence threshold | 5.00 ATR |
+| Prominence weighting | 70% incoming leg / 30% confirming reversal |
+| Candidate availability | Enforced |
+| Pivot validity through confirmation | Enforced |
+| Whole-window adaptive configuration | Disabled |
+
+## Core results
+
+| Version / Split | Predictions | TP | FP | FN | Precision | Recall | F1 | Macro Major-External F1 |
+|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|
+| v2.0 TRAIN | 357 | 97 | 260 | 7 | 0.2717 | 0.9327 | 0.4208 | 0.4610 |
+| v2.1 TRAIN | 108 | 88 | 20 | 16 | 0.8148 | 0.8462 | 0.8302 | 0.6495 |
+| v2.0 VALIDATION | 193 | 60 | 133 | 7 | 0.3109 | 0.8955 | 0.4615 | 0.4601 |
+| v2.1 VALIDATION | 57 | 54 | 3 | 13 | 0.9474 | 0.8060 | 0.8710 | 0.6051 |
+| v2.0 all calibration | 550 | 157 | 393 | 14 | 0.2855 | 0.9181 | 0.4355 | 0.4607 |
+| v2.1 all calibration | 165 | 142 | 23 | 29 | 0.8606 | 0.8304 | 0.8452 | 0.6347 |
+
+## Net change versus frozen v2.0
+
+| Measure | Change |
+|---|---:|
+| False positives | 393 → 23 (94.1% reduction) |
+| Predictions | 550 → 165 |
+| Precision | 0.2855 → 0.8606 |
+| Recall | 0.9181 → 0.8304 |
+| F1 | 0.4355 → 0.8452 |
+
+The recall reduction is intentional: v2.1 rejects many small fractal rotations that the draft policy does not consider structurally meaningful. The validation split retained 0.8060 recall while reaching 0.9474 precision.
+
+## TRAIN search
+
+### Structural reversal threshold
+
+| ATR threshold | Precision | Recall | F1 | FP |
+|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|
+| 2.4 | 0.6894 | 0.8750 | 0.7712 | 41 |
+| 2.6 | 0.7459 | 0.8750 | 0.8053 | 31 |
+| 2.8 | 0.8148 | 0.8462 | 0.8302 | 20 |
+| 3.0 | 0.8866 | 0.8269 | 0.8557 | 11 |
+
+`2.8` was selected because it maximised TRAIN F1 among candidates satisfying the frozen TRAIN recall floor of 0.84. Although `3.0` had higher F1, its recall of 0.8269 violated that constraint.
+
+### Structural prominence threshold
+
+| ATR threshold | TRAIN macro Major-External F1 |
+|---:|---:|
+| 4.4 | 0.6391 |
+| 4.6 | 0.6414 |
+| 4.8 | 0.6435 |
+| 5.0 | 0.6495 |
+
+`5.0` was selected on TRAIN only.
+
+## Performance by regime
+
+| Regime | Precision | Recall | F1 | FP | FN | Major-External F1 |
+|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|
+| HIGH_VOLATILITY | 0.8571 | 0.8571 | 0.8571 | 4 | 4 | 0.6061 |
+| LOW_VOLATILITY | 0.7407 | 0.7692 | 0.7547 | 7 | 6 | 0.5846 |
+| RANGE | 0.8333 | 0.8000 | 0.8163 | 4 | 5 | 0.6905 |
+| STRONG_BEARISH_TREND | 0.9333 | 0.9032 | 0.9180 | 2 | 3 | 0.4167 |
+| STRONG_BULLISH_TREND | 0.9615 | 0.7576 | 0.8475 | 1 | 8 | 0.7709 |
+| TREND_REVERSAL | 0.8333 | 0.8929 | 0.8621 | 5 | 3 | 0.7394 |
+
+The weakest location result is low-volatility structure (F1 0.7547). The weakest hierarchy result is strong bearish trend Major/External classification (macro F1 0.4167). Those are the next targeted research areas.
+
+## Error profile
+
+`predicted_type_errors` counts unmatched predictions plus location-matched predictions whose hierarchy/scope disagrees with truth. It is a semantic error profile, so its total can exceed location false positives.
+
+### Frozen v2.0
+
+- `MAJOR_NEUTRAL_HIGH`: 106
+- `MAJOR_INTERNAL_LOW`: 84
+- `MAJOR_NEUTRAL_LOW`: 81
+- `MAJOR_EXTERNAL_HIGH`: 80
+- `MAJOR_EXTERNAL_LOW`: 62
+- `MAJOR_INTERNAL_HIGH`: 62
+- `MINOR_INTERNAL_LOW`: 6
+- `MINOR_INTERNAL_HIGH`: 2
+
+### Tuned v2.1
+
+- `MINOR_INTERNAL_LOW`: 22
+- `MAJOR_EXTERNAL_HIGH`: 18
+- `MINOR_INTERNAL_HIGH`: 16
+- `MAJOR_EXTERNAL_LOW`: 13
+
+v2.1 eliminates the `NEUTRAL` structural category and stops nearly every local fractal from being promoted to Major. Remaining errors are concentrated in Minor/Internal rotations and Major/External hierarchy decisions.
+
+## Algorithm changes
+
+- Alternating reversal-confirmed structural pivot state machine.
+- ATR threshold frozen at the candidate pivot for prefix stability.
+- Same-side candidates replace the pending pivot only when more extreme.
+- Confirmation cannot precede fractal availability or structural reversal.
+- Pivot remains valid through the actual confirmation bar.
+- Major/Minor and Internal/External are derived from one structural prominence score.
+- v2.0 behavior is preserved behind version-gated configuration flags.
+
+## Reproduce
+
+```bash
+python scripts/validate_human_benchmark.py benchmarks/labels/XAUUSD_H1.human.json
+python scripts/tune_xauusd_h1.py
+pytest -q
+```
+
+Expected tests for this patch: `265 passed`.
+
+## Release decision
+
+Do not change the scanner default from v2.0 to v2.1 yet. First obtain independent label adjudication, create a locked TEST set from unseen later history, and evaluate v2.1 exactly once on that test release.
